
Thank you for your interest in contributing to Harmony!

## How to contribute
- Fork the repository, make your changes, and submit a pull request.
- All contributions are licensed under the MIT License.

## What to contribute
- Bugfixes, new features, documentation.
- Tests for new and existing features.
- Ideas via GitHub Issues or Discussions.

## Code Guidelines
- Write clear, modular code and comment non-obvious logic.
- Format Java to match standards (use Java 17).
- Add or update tests if you change logic.

## Before you PR
- Ensure builds pass with `./gradlew build`.
- Describe any breaking changes or new APIs.
